    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-and-coconut-basa-with-soy-lime-broccoli/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>broccoli</strong> into small florets</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Roll your<strong> lime[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-and-coconut-basa-with-soy-lime-broccoli/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-and-coconut-basa-with-soy-lime-broccoli/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the onion softens, chop your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed</strong> <strong>coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>creamed</strong> <strong>coconut </strong>in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-and-coconut-basa-with-soy-lime-broccoli/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>ground coriander </strong>and <strong>ground turmeric </strong>to the pan with the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-and-coconut-basa-with-soy-lime-broccoli/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chopped basa</strong>, <strong>coconut stock </strong>and <strong>saffron </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 4-5 min further or until cooked through \u2013 this is your<strong> saffron & coconut basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-and-coconut-basa-with-soy-lime-broccoli/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>broccoli florets</strong> to a heatproof bowl, then cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 4-5 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once tender, add your <strong>soy sauce</strong> with a squeeze of <strong>lime juice </strong>and a small knob of <strong>butter </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> soy lime broccoli</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime </strong>into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-and-coconut-basa-with-soy-lime-broccoli/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>saffron & coconut basa </strong>with the <strong>cooked rice </strong>and <strong>soy lime Tenderstem broccoli </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
